other_tests.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis; liver homogeneously hypodense consistent with fatty change; gallbladder distended with mild pericholecystic fluid, fat stranding, mild gallbladder wall thickening, and irregularity without frank perforation; small amount of free fluid in subhepatic space; normal pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and urinary bladder; scattered diverticula in colon; no lymphadenopathy; moderate atherosclerotic disease.
